    "§": "crwdns112298:0crwdne112298:0",
    "Koko is a (WIP) self-hosted media server written in Rust. At this point in time this is a learning project,\nand you": "crwdns112300:0crwdne112300:0",
    "SHOULD NOT": "crwdns112302:0crwdne112302:0",
    "use this for any purpose. I don’t know what I am doing and the code is probably terrible.\nThis is also": "crwdns112304:0crwdne112304:0",
    "NOT": "crwdns112306:0crwdne112306:0",
    "a functioning media server yet. Once it is, I will update this README.": "crwdns112308:0crwdne112308:0",
    "If you are interested in this project, please leave a star and watch the repository for updates.": "crwdns112310:0crwdne112310:0",
    "If you would like to contribute, please reach out on our": "crwdns112312:0crwdne112312:0",
    "discord": "crwdns112314:0crwdne112314:0",
    "server.": "crwdns112316:0crwdne112316:0",
    "Koko uses a YAML configuration file to set up the server.": "crwdns112318:0crwdne112318:0",
    "The file must be named": "crwdns112320:0crwdne112320:0",
    "settings.yml": "crwdns112322:0crwdne112322:0",
    "and be placed in the following location, depending on your OS.": "crwdns112324:0crwdne112324:0",
    "OS": "crwdns112326:0crwdne112326:0",
    "Location": "crwdns112328:0crwdne112328:0",
